Ask HN: Best media/resources for non-speculative crypto news and analysis?
text:
I'm interested in learning about interesting crypto projects - like aleph zero - but search results on sites like reddit or youtube usually revolve around price speculation. I was wondering where the best places are to get the technical angle, or progress on possible applications like remittances.

These are a couple of examples of the type of stuff I'm looking for:

* https://rationalreminder.ca/understanding-crypto

* https://technium.transistor.fm/episodes/lightning-network-payments-so-small-its-a-stream-s03-e10

Ask HN: Is Vivoo the Next Theranos?
text:
Vivoo https://vivoo.io/ is a urine test that works with smartphones (photo taken of colour-changing patches) and claims to give health insights across multiple indicators.

It’s an interesting idea and I’ve placed an order. But I have nagging suspicions about this sort of thing after the Theranos scandal. Any medical professionals here that could comment?

title: Ask HN: Is Clojure Dead?
text:
Hi, I don't see much about clojure over past 2 years or so. Same goes for other industry functional languages (e.g. elixir, scala, F#).

Are they just in later stages of hype cycle or are they dying out the same way perl did?

For better or worse most of news/fuzz these days seem to be about Rust (not that this translates to actual job postings though).

PS: Asking because I want to delve into a functional language but I cannot bring myself to do this seriously if it doesn't translate into market value.
